parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in costly repairs or even accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes a quarter of oil additional every 3000 miles
frequent oil top-offs
oil leaks
or unusual engine noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag System Failure (Driver Side Front Door Harness Issue)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the deployment of airbags in non-crash scenarios, causing injuries or accidents, or failure to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in increased risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Airbag light intermittently flashing or staying on all the time
open circuit in the driver side front door harness
airbag sensor malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Failure (Concentric Slave Cylinder and Clutch Master Cylinder Issues)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear
unusual smells or smoke from the clutch area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle catching fire while unattended can cause significant damage, pose a risk to surrounding people and property, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly catches fire while parked
with no warning signs or symptoms beforehand.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected cracking of the windshield can cause startle, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The windshield cracks suddenly
without any apparent cause
making a loud noise
and resulting in a distinctive crack pattern (e.g.
"J" shape or a line across the middle).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to occupants, especially in severe accidents.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
occupants may experience injuries or fatalities that could have been prevented or mitigated by airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can increase the stopping distance, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes take longer than usual to kick-in
the brakes are soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected
the brakes fail to engage properly.
